          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Ned Bass",
          "email": "bass6@llnl.gov",
          "date": "2012-11-07 20:46:13.000000000",
          "tz": -480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Ned Bass",
          "email": "bass6@llnl.gov",
          "date": "2012-11-07 21:41:00.000000000",
          "tz": -480
        },
        "subject": "LU-2164 utils: mkfs.lustre segfaults if no \"/\" in dataset name",
        "message": "LU-2164 utils: mkfs.lustre segfaults if no \"/\" in dataset name\n\nmkfs.lustre incorrectly assumes that the libzfs function\nzfs_name_valid() disallows filesystem names without a \"/\", and so uses\nthe result of strrchr(pool, '/') without a NULL check.  In fact\ndataset names without a / are permitted, as in the case of commands\nlike\n\n   zfs get all tank\n\nwhere a pool tank is treated like a dataset.  The leads to a segfault\nif mkfs.lustre is given a dataset name without a /.  Since lustre\ndatasets are always created as children of a pool, add a separate\ncheck for a missing slash and print an error if it's missing.\n\nSigned-off-by: Ned Bass <bass6@llnl.gov>\nChange-Id: Ic7bede9ca19d646f64d2f166f189fa6822a70fe3\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
